t: Pentland Brands / Canterbury of New Zealand
s: November 22, 2024 - Canterbury is the world’s original rugby brand. Founded in New Zealand in 1904, it joined the Pentland family in 2012. Canterbury makes highly technical products that improve performance, as well as casual apparel and official fan merchandise.

March 2, 2025 - Canterbury of New Zealand was established in 1904, producing garments in Canterbury, New Zealand. The company made military uniforms during the First World War, before producing kit for the All Blacks. The brand's tagline is "Committed To The Game".
